7:
Hard Rock Magic, let's go! One, two,
three, four!
20:
Who gave you permission to
practice here anyway? Find a
concert hall or something!
26:
But we want the whole world to hear
our new song! You know, the one
Old Mister Metal wrote for us!
30:
Eugh, I'm gonna go deaf at this
rate... Stella, you do something
about this.
51:
Cowdy. So this is where you were
hiding, Hard Rock Magic.
57:
You've gotta be kidding me. Light,
tell me I'm hallucinating.
61:
I'm afraid not. Judging by her
animal companion and general
demeanor, she must be like Noenne
and her friends...
65:
In other words, one of the idols
participating in their Battle Royale:
All Star Smash!
69:
Allow me to explain! Battle Royale:
All Star Smash, or BRASS for short, is
a competition held between the
twelve states in our world!
70:
Consider it diplomacy through song
and dance battles. Idol warfare to
prevent idle warfare!
74:
You're even joined by the Cosmic
Beasts of the Hare and Tiger. How is
this possible?
78:
Er, about that... This is actually
another world, separate from ours.
There's no twelve states here.
82:
Which also means Light and Nimbus
aren't Cosmic Beasts. Don't worry,
we were confused at first too!
88:
Hello, Beaucy. This is Starview
Village, a vista that overlooks other
worlds.
92:
Cowdy. I suppose Noenne must be
speaking the truth. I don't feel any
Cosmic Energy from any of you.
96:
Beaucy, Cacow, you're the
Chateaubrilliand Duo! How did you
get here? Don't tell me you both
lost...
105: Us, lose? You must be joking.
107: In fact, we won. BRASS is over.
113:
Wh-what?! No more BRASS? But...
our goal of winning it...
123:
But you better watch out! We're
taking home the win next time!
127:
As moo-ving as your little speech
was, I'm afraid that won't be
possible. BRASS is over—forever.
129:
I made sure of it by sealing all the
other Cosmic Beasts away.
133:
The only one still roaming free is
you, Kapipi. But that will change
soon enough.
139:
Get ready, Noenne! Battle Royale: All
Star Smash, loading complete!
144:
I'll put an end to idols and all this
BRASS nonsense.
147: No escape from crossing fate! GO!
152:
Beaucy, what do you mean by that?!
What's your end goal here?
155:
I have no obligation to explain
anything to a filet minion like you.
161:
Curses... Noenne! Beaucy is a top
gravure idol—you know, the ones
that are basically pin-up models!
We can't win against her!
165:
You think putting distance between
us gives you a fighting chance?
Fools.
181:
Best not to question it. Y'know, for
your own sanity's sake.
187:
She's too strong! Is this the power of
a top idol?!
193:
I won't let you... take away idols... or
the BRASS!
202:
Whoa there, Stella. You don't wanna
get caught up in this. Trust me.
207: Rgh, is this truly the end for us?
210:
...Why haven't you struck us down?
Getting cold feet?
213:
I'm curious. The last time we met,
you weren't even worth roasting
over an open fire.
215:
But somehow, you've managed to
put on a prime performance. How
did you come to improve so much?
219:
I'm back! Managed to grab a ton of
great New Year's deals! We're gonna
be so well stocked—
233:
Producer? Now it all makes sense.
You're the reason for their
improvement.
238:
U-uh... Would someone mind filling
me in?
242:
Why bother? I've been here since the
start, and I've got zero clue what's
going on.
251:
Ohhh, so she's someone from BRASS,
huh? I think I'm starting to get the
picture...
256:
If producers exist in other worlds,
then that means idols must also
exist.
259:
I've decided to postpone your
sealing. For the time being, I will
study the idols of other worlds.
264: Works for me. Stella, do your thing.
269:
Beaucy. Cacow. Welcome to
Starview Village.
274:
It behooves me to accept your
welcome.
